The President Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), on Saturday, condoled with General Aliyu Gusau (retd.) on the passing of Tukur Gusau, a younger brother to the former Minister of Defence. This is according to a statement by the President’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, titled ‘President Buhari pays tribute to Tukur, General Gusau’s younger brother.’ In a message to Gen. Gusau who was also a former National Security Adviser, Buhari described the deceased businessman as a rare blessing to his family and community. He said, ‘’He cared for everyone in a special way, becoming a pillar of support and a prized asset to the family and community. My thoughts are with the family of the deceased and to you (General Gusau) as well as the government and people of Zamfara State.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com